                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 5.417,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has the opinion of the court in two cases this morning."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 5.417,
                        "stop": 304.056,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15068,
                            "name": "Samuel A. Alito, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/samuel_alito_jr",
                            "last_name": "Alito",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2712,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1138687200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2712"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32684,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44799,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/samuel_a_alito_jr_1.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 3531,
                            "identifier": "samuel_alito_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 5.417,
                                "stop": 12.29,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The first case is Ohio v. Clark, Number 13-1352."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 12.29,
                                "stop": 23.021,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "This case presents the question whether the Confrontation Clause of the Sixth Amendment bars the admission of out-of-court statements that were made by a young abused child to his teachers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 23.021,
                                "stop": 26.382,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The petitioner in this case is Darius Clark."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.382,
                                "stop": 36.959,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "He sent his girlfriend from Ohio to the District of Columbia to engage in prostitution, and he agreed to care for her two young children while she was gone."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.959,
                                "stop": 45.061,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The next day Clark took one of the children, a three-year-old boy L.P., to preschool."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.061,
                                "stop": 50.679,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Shortly after L.P. arrived at school, his teachers noticed injuries on his face."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.679,
                                "stop": 54.94,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They asked him what happened, and he identified Clark as his abuser."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.94,
                                "stop": 67.89,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The teachers notified authorities, and Clark was eventually arrested and indicted on multiple counts relating to his abuse of L.P. and also his girlfriend\u0027s 18-month-old daughter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.89,
                                "stop": 77.761,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "At trial, state prosecutors introduced the statements that L.P. made to his teachers, but L.P. was not able to testify because of his young age."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 77.761,
                                "stop": 95.239,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Clark objected arguing that the state\u0027s use of these out of court statements would violate his rights under the Sixth Amendment\u0027s Confrontation Clause, which provides that in all criminal prosecutions the accused shall enjoy the right to be confronted with the witnesses against him."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.239,
                                "stop": 99.105,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The trial judge rejected Clark\u0027s argument and admitted the evidence."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.105,
                                "stop": 105.943,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The jury convicted Clark on multiple counts, and he was sentenced to 28 years imprisonment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.943,
                                "stop": 116.802,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "A State Appellate Court reversed the conviction holding that the state\u0027s use of L.P.\u0027s statements violated the Confrontation Clause, and the Supreme Court of Ohio affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.802,
                                "stop": 131.924,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We disagree. In Crawford v. Washington, the Court took a new approach to the interpretation of the Confrontation Clause, and this has spawned a regular stream of cases in this Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 131.924,
                                "stop": 149.43,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Crawford held that the Confrontation Clause generally prohibits the introduction of \u201ctestimonial statements\u201d by witnesses who do not appear at trial unless the witness is unavailable to testify and the defendant had a prior opportunity to cross-examine the witness."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.43,
                                "stop": 160.242,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In later cases we have explained that a statement is testimonial if its primary purpose was to create an out of court substitute for trial testimony."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 160.242,
                                "stop": 167,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When conducting that primary purpose inquiry, we consider all of the relevant circumstances."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167,
                                "stop": 172.705,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "If there is no primary purpose then a statement cannot violate the Confrontation Clause."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.705,
                                "stop": 182.174,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Considering all of the relevant circumstances here, it is clear that L.P.\u0027s statements were not testimonial, and therefore the Confrontation Clause does not apply."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 182.174,
                                "stop": 193.272,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "L.P.\u0027s statements and his teachers\u0027 questions occurred during an ongoing emergency, and the conversation was aimed at resolving a serious threat to L.P.\u0027s safety."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.272,
                                "stop": 200.209,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Nothing about the discussion suggested that its primary purpose was to gather evidence for Clark\u0027s prosecution."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 200.209,
                                "stop": 215.148,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It is also significant that the conversation occurred immediately after the teachers noticed L.P.\u0027s injuries and that it took place in the informal setting of a preschool classroom and cafeteria."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 215.148,
                                "stop": 223.664,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Those circumstances were markedly different from the formal police interrogations we have found problematic in other cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.664,
                                "stop": 243.779,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "L.P.\u0027s age is also highly relevant. Statements by young children will rarely, if ever, qualify as testimonial because most young children do not understand the criminal justice system enough to know, let alone intend, that their out of court statements will be used as evidence in a criminal trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 243.779,
                                "stop": 255.562,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Moreover, there is strong historical evidence that statements in circumstances like these, where a young child reports abuse to an adult, would have been admissible in criminal cases at common law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 255.562,
                                "stop": 268.976,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Finally, although we decline to hold that statements to individuals who are not law enforcement officers are categorically outside the Confrontation Clause\u0027s reach, it is relevant that L.P. was speaking to his teachers and not the police."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 268.976,
                                "stop": 279.609,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Statements to individuals who are not charged with uncovering and prosecuting crimes are much less likely to be testimonial than statements to law enforcement officers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 279.609,
                                "stop": 287.628,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For these reasons we hold that the Confrontation Clause did not prohibit prosecutors from introducing L.P.\u0027s statements during Clark\u0027s criminal trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 287.628,
                                "stop": 291.203,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The judgment of the Supreme Court of Ohio is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 291.203,
                                "stop": 304.056,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment, in which Justice Ginsburg has joined. Justice Thomas has also filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
